> Newer glibc has catchsegv (haven't found any documentation, but its
> interesting) --
It's just LD_PRELOAD (man ld.so) and libSegFault.so, which installs
(among others) SIGSEGV handler, see "glibc/sysdeps/generic/segfault.c".
